  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So to-- for-- to-- in that sense, the poverty, and I had an encounter with that poverty when I traveled to Poland on my father's behalf to collect-- to collect, if possible, non-- the non-- non-honored promissory notes that were coming back for good that people have bought from us and never had a chance of paying for.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I had an encounter to see Jewish existence in those small townships and hamlets in the role, as it was, not as you read it in a book or as it being [INAUDIBLE] by-- by a writer who wants to put the-- the best-- the best face on it and so on.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I've got pictures in my mind of Jewish shops-- little shops next to one another with the [HEBREW] people in their little beards and little Hasidic caps, standing there, pale faced, drawn.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The few pieces of merchandise that was on their-- on their shelves were put in such a way to cover the emptiness of the shelves so that there is some sort-- and those pieces-- a few pieces of rolls of material there did not belong to them.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It wasn't theirs.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Like the-- the ones that we gave them, they took on credit and never-- and never could pay for them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Never could pay for them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "If-- if they managed to put one meal a day on the table, they were doing well.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So hopeless, some of the life of these people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And that's why people emigrated in such numbers in the-- in the end of last century and the beginning of this century if there was opportunity to go anywhere because-- because the-- the-- the-- the economic base in most places was very, very unstable, if at all.",
      "word_count": 47
    }
  ],
